  "prompt": "Can tax exemption be availed on tax saving FD for the entire tenure of 5 years by investing 1.5 lakhs in the 1st year?",
  "response": "The tax exemption on a tax-saving Fixed Deposit (FD) applies to the amount you invest in the FD in the year of investment, up to the limit specified under Section 80C of the Income Tax Act, which is \u20b91.5 lakhs. Let's break this down:\n\n1. **Year of Investment**: When you invest \u20b91.5 lakhs in a tax-saving FD in the first year, you claim the tax exemption for that year. The exemption amount for that year is up to \u20b91.5 lakhs.\n\n2. **Tax Exemption Claim**: For the subsequent years, you cannot claim a tax exemption for the initial \u20b91.5 lakhs invested in the first year again under Section 80C. The tax exemption is a one-time benefit on the amount invested each year.\n\n3. **Fixed Tenure Benefit**: The tax-saving FD has a lock-in period of 5 years, meaning you cannot withdraw the funds before the completion of 5 years. However, the tax exemption under Section 80C is available only once, in the financial year when the investment is made.\n\n4. **Reinvestment**: If you wish to claim tax exemption in the following years as well, you would need to make new investments into Section 80C eligible instruments each year.\n\nTherefore, you can avail of the tax exemption for the amount invested only in the financial year in which the investment is made, not for the entire tenure of 5 years unless new investments are made each year.",
